      "description": "The ensemble score boundary used to classify a trace: score \u2265 threshold \u2192 ATTACK, score < threshold \u2192 normal. The score is 0.7 \u00d7 RobustScaled(VAE reconstruction error) + 0.3 \u00d7 RobustScaled(Isolation Forest score). After scaling, typical normal traces cluster around 0; attack traces score higher. The threshold is negative (-0.0132) because the model's normal-vs-attack gap is small (val AUC 0.66 vs paper target 0.92 \u2014 only kernel 5.12 normal data available). Was selected on the validation set by maximising F1. Raise it to reduce false positives; lower it to reduce missed attacks."
    },
